    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A milky beverage produced by soaking, grinding, and boiling dried soy beans. It is a traditional staple of Chinese and Japanese cuisine and has been promoted as a substitute for cow’s milk elsewhere.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
